95cbd2e1-c9e8-41c4-a2cc-60541dee3649.content: <p>got from web search</p><p> </p><p><i><strong>PRODUCT VISION </strong>— what you want your final product to be</i></p><p><i><strong>STRATEGY </strong>— execution plan detailing what you need to do to meet the requirements</i></p><p><i><strong>GOAL </strong>— objective to be measured by specific metrics</i></p><p><i><strong>INITIATIVE </strong>— set of features to be implemented to achieve the GOAL</i></p><p><i><strong>FEATURE </strong>— a piece of a product: functionality or a 3rd party application</i></p><p><i><strong>TIME FRAME</strong> — time necessary (approximate value) for a certain goal/feature to be completed</i></p><p><i><strong>STATUS MARKER</strong> — used for work progress</i></p><p><i><strong>METRICS </strong>— measurement of goals, e.g. organic traffic or churn rate.</i></p>
